      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right to be concerned about the potential impact on your bottom line, and research suggests that small businesses are indeed more vulnerable to the effects of a higher minimum wage. Studies have shown that a significant increase in the minimum wage can lead to reduced employment rates, particularly among low-skilled workers, and even business closures. In fact, many experts argue that a higher minimum wage can be a job killer for small businesses, especially in low-cost-of-living areas.",
